ZCZC GE94
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
SUNDAY TO WEDNESDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND
COASTGUARD AGENCY AT 082300 UTC
THROUGH SUNDAY EVENING A DPN LOW PRESSURE AREA 974 WILL
BE CENTRED NEAR HEBRIDES. DURING MONDAY THE LOW PRESSURE
CENTRE WILL MIGRATE TO VIKING AND FILL WITH A TRANSITORY
RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE APPROACHING IRELAND. THIS RIDGE
WILL CROSS THE BRITISH ISLES ON TUESDAY BEFORE ANOTHER
DPN LOW PRESSURE CENTRE WILL CROSS SERN IRELAND AND
BRITAIN LATER TUESDAY THEN CROSS THE N SEA ON WEDNESDAY.
A LARGE COMPLEX AREA OF LOW PRESSURE WILL LIE FM UK TO
ICELAND AND NORWAY THROUGH WEDNESDAY MORNING BEFORE
PRESSURE RISES IN W LATER WEDNESDAY. DURING SUNDAY
EVENING AND MONDAY WINDS WILL BE STRG AT TIMES IN THE N
SEA WITH GALES IN THE S FOR A TIME INCLUDING THAMES
DOVER AND WIGHT. NW WINDS WILL INCREASE TO NEAR GALE IN
FORTIES CROMARTY AND FAIR ISLE LATER. W WINDS WILL BE
STRG AT TIMES THROUGH TUESDAY AND WEDNESDAY WITH GALES
OR SEV GALES AND POSS STORMS DEVELOPING IN THE S LATER
TUESDAY AND WEDNESDAY
NNNN